Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Send Message (UC2), Validate Message Content (UC5), include relationship from UC2 to UC5
   Explanation: "Validate Message Content" (UC5) is an inclusion use case that is included by only one use case ("Send Message" / UC2). It is not associated with any actor directly. It does not include or extend any other use case, is not extended by any use case, and is neither a generalization nor a specialization of any use case. "Validate Message Content" does not represent a complete, independently valuable service to any actor — it is merely a decomposed sub-step of sending a message. This is a textbook instance of Functional Decomposition via the include relationship, where a single use case's internal behavior has been artificially split into a separate inclusion use case that provides no observable standalone result to any user.
